As of the 2020 census, there were 6,685 people and 2,806 households, and residing in the borough. The population density was {{convert|6,618.8|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The [[Race and ethnicity in the United States census|racial makeup]] of the borough was 90.6% White, 2.9% African American, 0.4% Asian, 4.0% Hispanic or Latino, and 5.1% from two or more races.

There were 2,806 households, with the persons per household being 2.37.

The median income for a household in the borough was $75,054. The [[per capita income]] for the borough was $38,565. About 6.6% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=United States Census Bureau |date=2020 |title=Quickfacts West View borough, Pennsylvania |url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/westviewboroughpennsylvania }}</ref>

